import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zipcodes_by_state = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    zipcodes_by_state = zipcodes_by_state.sort_values(by='zip_code', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(zipcodes_by_state['state'], zipcodes_by_state['zip_code'], color='blue')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], s=1, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    county_zip_counts = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(county_zip_counts.index, county_zip_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('County')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different counties?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_counts = data.groupby('state')['city'].nunique()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(city_counts.index, city_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Cities')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of cities across different states?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
